                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On September 13 and 14, Percy C. Spender, Australian Minister for External
                    Affairs, visited Washington en route to New York to attend the Fifth Session of
                    the United Nations General Assembly. He met with President Truman on the 13th
                    and with a Congressional delegation the following day. On September 18, Spender
                    conferred with Secretary of State Acheson in New York. For memoranda of these
                    conversations, which dealt in part with regional security arrangements and other
                    matters pertaining to the East Asian-Pacific area, see <ref target="#pg_212"
                        >pages 212</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
